nodes.bodyText: What's the harm in just initializing the return stack with the proper size always? It would stop us from having to add this extra boolean parameter here.
you're right this makes the code more simple and clean

I see that this is modeled after the existing isValidJumpDestination. What do you think about moving the caching logic for both to the fields themselves using Suppliers.memoize? I think it'd make it easier to read and getting rid of a null in the code makes angels sing :)
I think you're right, this would be too impactful. Looks good as is then :)
Why do we want a 0 capacity return stack as the default?
I just changed with the default size of 1023 as in the EIP
Depending on the discussion with the other comments, we might not need this constructor.
